flowRoot.flowPara: Knowledge models can be conveniently managed in the Wizard. Editor is a tool to interactively create, edit, or delete parts of a KM, including creating new KM from scratch or as a customization of existing one. After the changes are done, a new version of KM can be published with the use of semantic versioning. In case that the parent KM of the customization gets updated, you can very easily migrate your customization by just picking the changes you want to adopt. Until you migrate, the published KM will be still available but marked as outdated. The updates get to all customizations in the KM forest in this efficient but simple way.
